95
00:04:13,186 --> 00:04:15,255
Keep moving, no mumbling.

96
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:16,990
Do as I say.

97
00:04:16,990 --> 00:04:18,625
♪

98
00:04:18,625 --> 00:04:19,659
Come on.

99
00:04:19,659 --> 00:04:24,030
Only one of us can go,
so you wait here, Mocchi.

100
00:04:24,030 --> 00:04:26,500
‐Mocchi comes!
‐Can't happen.

101
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:28,602
If we both go and
we both get caught,

102
00:04:28,602 --> 00:04:30,637
then who'll be left
to find the Phoenix?

103
00:04:30,637 --> 00:04:33,006
‐Mocchi don't care.
‐You stay here.

104
00:04:33,006 --> 00:04:35,542
Mocchi don't want to,
Mocchi don't want to!

105
00:04:35,542 --> 00:04:38,578
Mocchi, Mocchi,
Mocchi don't want to!

106
00:04:38,578 --> 00:04:40,447
I don't want to!

107
00:04:40,447 --> 00:04:42,916
Mocchi!

108
00:04:42,916 --> 00:04:45,919
Mocchi, this is important.

109
00:04:45,919 --> 00:04:46,987
Listen.

110
00:04:46,987 --> 00:04:49,055
If I or the others don't return,

111
00:04:49,055 --> 00:04:51,591
someone has to find the Phoenix.

112
00:04:51,591 --> 00:04:54,060
♪

113
00:04:54,060 --> 00:04:55,562
Please.

114
00:04:55,562 --> 00:05:03,370
♪

115
00:05:03,370 --> 00:05:07,274
Our hearts'll
always be together.

116
00:05:07,274 --> 00:05:09,176
Mocchi wait right here!

117
00:05:09,176 --> 00:05:13,947
Mocchi, Mocchi, Mocchi!

118
00:05:13,947 --> 00:05:15,549
Mocchi!

119
00:05:15,549 --> 00:05:20,086
♪

120
00:05:20,086 --> 00:05:21,721
(gasps)

121
00:05:21,721 --> 00:05:27,460
♪

122
00:05:27,460 --> 00:05:29,496
They must be guards.

123
00:05:29,496 --> 00:05:34,835
♪

124
00:05:34,835 --> 00:05:36,102
Huh?

125
00:05:36,102 --> 00:05:38,538
Sounds like a sound,
I'll go look.

126
00:05:38,538 --> 00:05:43,410
♪

127
00:05:43,410 --> 00:05:44,711
Huh?

128
00:05:44,711 --> 00:05:46,913
♪

129
00:05:46,913 --> 00:05:48,648
Spooky place.

130
00:05:48,648 --> 00:05:55,689
♪

131
00:05:55,689 --> 00:05:56,590
Oh!

132
00:05:56,590 --> 00:05:59,726
It could be...

133
00:05:59,726 --> 00:06:01,528
Yeah‐‐whoa!

134
00:06:01,528 --> 00:06:08,368
♪

135
00:06:08,368 --> 00:06:10,637
This is terrible.

136
00:06:10,637 --> 00:06:11,805
Genki!

137
00:06:11,805 --> 00:06:13,773
It's about time, kid.

138
00:06:13,773 --> 00:06:15,108
Is everyone okay?

139
00:06:15,108 --> 00:06:16,776
We thought it would take
you forever and a day

140
00:06:16,776 --> 00:06:18,478
to climb out of that canyon.

141
00:06:18,478 --> 00:06:21,982
No way, it was a piece
of cake for me and Mocchi.

142
00:06:21,982 --> 00:06:24,517
Yup, same old Genki!

143
00:06:24,517 --> 00:06:27,020
Hey, could you keep
it down over there?

144
00:06:27,020 --> 00:06:28,989
It's great you're back
and everything, kid,

145
00:06:28,989 --> 00:06:30,924
but I'm trying to catch
a little shuteye.

146
00:06:30,924 --> 00:06:33,260
It's no bed of roses
here, you know.

147
00:06:33,260 --> 00:06:35,695
It's no good pretending
you don't care, Tiger.

148
00:06:35,695 --> 00:06:38,265
You've been worried
more than anybody.

149
00:06:38,265 --> 00:06:39,232
Hm?

150
00:06:39,232 --> 00:06:40,467
Says who?

151
00:06:40,467 --> 00:06:42,836
Says me!

152
00:06:42,836 --> 00:06:47,474
Fighting solves nothing and
doesn't get us out of here.

153
00:06:47,474 --> 00:06:49,309
All right, I'm glad
you're back, kid,

154
00:06:49,309 --> 00:06:50,610
okay, everyone?

155
00:06:50,610 --> 00:06:53,380
Now, why don't we get ourselves
out of this insufferable place?

156
00:06:53,380 --> 00:06:54,915
Torpedo attacks sound good.

157
00:06:54,915 --> 00:06:57,484
You're forgetting about their
habit of taking hostages,

158
00:06:57,484 --> 00:06:59,319
which has served them
quite well in the past,

159
00:06:59,319 --> 00:07:02,022
if you care to remember, Tiger.

160
00:07:02,022 --> 00:07:03,123
You two.

161
00:07:03,123 --> 00:07:05,692
As it turns out, you're
probably both right.

162
00:07:05,692 --> 00:07:07,193
We can use a torpedo attack

163
00:07:07,193 --> 00:07:09,396
and make sure all
of the slaves leave

164
00:07:09,396 --> 00:07:11,765
so Pixie can't
take any hostages.

165
00:07:11,765 --> 00:07:15,035
Lucky for us there're only
two guards watching this place

166
00:07:15,035 --> 00:07:17,704
and they're both a few
rocks short of a full load.

167
00:07:17,704 --> 00:07:19,339
‐Hey, you there.
‐Huh?

168
00:07:19,339 --> 00:07:21,274
I heard every word.

169
00:07:21,274 --> 00:07:22,375
Who are you?

170
00:07:22,375 --> 00:07:23,677
I'm Rocko.

171
00:07:23,677 --> 00:07:27,314
Sounds like you're planning
to blow this pop stand.

172
00:07:27,314 --> 00:07:29,015
You bet we are.

173
00:07:29,015 --> 00:07:31,318
Pixie and Big Blue
are tough customers.

174
00:07:31,318 --> 00:07:33,553
Yeah, but my name
happens to be Genki,

175
00:07:33,553 --> 00:07:36,556
and I have no intention
of letting Pixie and Big Blue

176
00:07:36,556 --> 00:07:38,124
get the best of me, Rocko.

177
00:07:38,124 --> 00:07:40,393
They tried once, and
I'm here to tell you

178
00:07:40,393 --> 00:07:42,028
it did not work.

179
00:07:42,028 --> 00:07:45,498
I hope you have an awful lot
of good monster attacks, Genki.

180
00:07:45,498 --> 00:07:47,500
Yup, we got 'em.

181
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:48,702
We sure do.

182
00:07:48,702 --> 00:07:51,504
♪

183
00:07:51,504 --> 00:07:53,573
Right, I'm in.

184
00:07:53,573 --> 00:07:57,177
I say we throw in with these
kids and their monster pals.

185
00:07:57,177 --> 00:07:58,712
Objections?

186
00:07:58,712 --> 00:08:02,615
How about Pixie's
revenge if we fail?

187
00:08:02,615 --> 00:08:05,852
And don't forget about Big Blue.

188
00:08:05,852 --> 00:08:09,122
But the alternative
is to be slaves in here

189
00:08:09,122 --> 00:08:11,124
for the rest of our lives.

190
00:08:11,124 --> 00:08:12,592
Not much of a life.

191
00:08:12,592 --> 00:08:15,428
Yeah, but I'm
against pain, myself.

192
00:08:15,428 --> 00:08:18,098
I miss the scent
of a nice rose.

193
00:08:18,098 --> 00:08:19,232
Huh?

194
00:08:19,232 --> 00:08:21,601
What about a butterfly
on a summer morning?

195
00:08:21,601 --> 00:08:22,702
That's right.

196
00:08:22,702 --> 00:08:24,904
While we're slaving away
in here mining disks,

197
00:08:24,904 --> 00:08:26,806
there's a whole world out
there that's going by

198
00:08:26,806 --> 00:08:29,743
and we're gonna miss it
altogether if we don't act.

199
00:08:29,743 --> 00:08:31,544
Let's go for it!

200
00:08:31,544 --> 00:08:32,812
Yeah!

201
00:08:32,812 --> 00:08:33,980
Come to think of it,

202
00:08:33,980 --> 00:08:36,616
the smell of fresh‐baked
bread is awfully nice.

203
00:08:36,616 --> 00:08:38,918
Yeah!

204
00:08:38,918 --> 00:08:40,053
Woo!

205
00:08:40,787 --> 00:08:42,222
♪ Monsters ♪

206
00:08:42,222 --> 00:08:43,823
♪ Monsters rule ♪

207
00:08:43,823 --> 00:08:45,392
♪ Get a disk, take a risk ♪

208
00:08:45,392 --> 00:08:46,960
♪ Spin it fast
through the past ♪

209
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:48,695
♪ Unlock it and claim
it, you can tame it ♪

210
00:08:50,196 --> 00:08:52,399
♪ Find a Seed Sister,
charming but frightening ♪

211
00:08:52,399 --> 00:08:53,767
♪ Unlock 'em all ♪

212
00:08:53,767 --> 00:08:55,769
♪ Or the Usaba,
quicker than lightning ♪

213
00:08:55,769 --> 00:08:56,936
♪ Unlock 'em all ♪

214
00:08:56,936 --> 00:08:59,039
♪ There's evil Hare
and his captain ♪

215
00:08:59,039 --> 00:09:00,373
♪ Unlock your disk ♪

216
00:09:00,373 --> 00:09:02,742
♪ They'd love to fight
like Pirate Dragons ♪

217
00:09:02,742 --> 00:09:03,977
♪ Unlock your disk ♪

218
00:09:03,977 --> 00:09:05,745
♪ Mighty they battle,
mighty they fall ♪

219
00:09:05,745 --> 00:09:07,914
♪ These monsters rule,
unlock 'em all ♪

220
00:09:07,914 --> 00:09:10,216
♪ Monsters rule ♪

221
00:09:13,586 --> 00:09:16,022
Took you long enough,
what was the noise?

222
00:09:16,022 --> 00:09:17,357
Beats me.

223
00:09:17,357 --> 00:09:19,492
Very interesting!

224
00:09:19,492 --> 00:09:20,460
In my opinion,

225
00:09:20,460 --> 00:09:24,064
this could be the
world's eighth wonder.

226
00:09:24,064 --> 00:09:26,232
‐Who are you?
‐How'd you get in?

227
00:09:26,232 --> 00:09:29,169
Oh my, they've spotted me!

228
00:09:29,169 --> 00:09:31,271
(growling)

229
00:09:31,271 --> 00:09:33,940
Come and get me,
onion monsters!

230
00:09:33,940 --> 00:09:35,842
Who are you calling an onion?

231
00:09:35,842 --> 00:09:38,611
Hey, ogre heads, over here!

232
00:09:38,611 --> 00:09:41,614
(growling, sizzling)

233
00:09:41,614 --> 00:09:44,484
♪

234
00:09:44,484 --> 00:09:47,487
Successful torpedo attack.

235
00:09:47,487 --> 00:09:50,290
Ah!

236
00:09:50,290 --> 00:09:52,625
(locks click)

237
00:09:52,625 --> 00:09:54,360
Mission accomplished.

238
00:09:54,360 --> 00:09:57,897
‐Is everybody ready?
‐Yeah!

239
00:09:57,897 --> 00:10:01,634
♪

240
00:10:01,634 --> 00:10:05,572
The exit is near‐‐
quiet, everybody.

241
00:10:05,572 --> 00:10:07,207
Huh?

242
00:10:07,207 --> 00:10:08,942
♪

243
00:10:08,942 --> 00:10:10,944
Mocchi!

244
00:10:10,944 --> 00:10:13,646
Pixie's gotta be the
meanest monster ever.

245
00:10:13,646 --> 00:10:16,549
Talk to me!

246
00:10:16,549 --> 00:10:19,319
Mo...cchi!

247
00:10:19,319 --> 00:10:21,521
sinister chuckle)

248
00:10:21,521 --> 00:10:23,423
(all growl)

249
00:10:23,423 --> 00:10:25,959
♪

250
00:10:25,959 --> 00:10:27,694
Pixie, listen.

251
00:10:27,694 --> 00:10:29,996
I know it wasn't
right of me to hit you,

252
00:10:29,996 --> 00:10:31,431
but you didn't need
to take it out

253
00:10:31,431 --> 00:10:33,233
on poor Mocchi.

254
00:10:33,233 --> 00:10:35,835
You humans have been
punishing us monsters

255
00:10:35,835 --> 00:10:38,938
for years, and now you
know what it feels like.

256
00:10:38,938 --> 00:10:39,906
Huh?

257
00:10:39,906 --> 00:10:42,709
You don't have
a clue how it feels

258
00:10:42,709 --> 00:10:45,111
to be born into bondage.

259
00:10:45,111 --> 00:10:46,880
♪

260
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:51,751
Greedy humans used
to rule this land.

261
00:10:51,751 --> 00:10:55,188
Rocko, did the humans here
used to imprison the monsters?

262
00:10:55,188 --> 00:10:56,222
Yes.

263
00:10:56,222 --> 00:10:57,891
There was a despicable ruler

264
00:10:57,891 --> 00:11:00,293
who captured many monsters
to excavate the ruins,

265
00:11:00,293 --> 00:11:03,663
looking for anything
that was worth money.

266
00:11:03,663 --> 00:11:04,831
That's terrible.

267
00:11:04,831 --> 00:11:06,399
And we revolted.

268
00:11:06,399 --> 00:11:07,700
But, Pixie, don't you see

269
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:09,102
that now you've
done to the humans

270
00:11:09,102 --> 00:11:12,739
what you despised
so much yourselves?

271
00:11:12,739 --> 00:11:15,575
But this time,
it's for a purpose.

272
00:11:15,575 --> 00:11:17,610
A... purpose?

273
00:11:17,610 --> 00:11:20,180
Master Moo's purpose!

274
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:23,249
♪

275
00:11:23,249 --> 00:11:26,319
Master Moo made us
part of his family,

276
00:11:26,319 --> 00:11:29,756
and for the first time,
monsters belonged.

277
00:11:29,756 --> 00:11:31,791
We were baddies.

278
00:11:31,791 --> 00:11:33,493
We had value.

279
00:11:33,493 --> 00:11:37,931
Family fills a hole
that Golem understands.

280
00:11:37,931 --> 00:11:38,998
You do?

281
00:11:38,998 --> 00:11:41,401
You have sad eyes, Pixie.

282
00:11:41,401 --> 00:11:44,270
You were lonesome,
so you joined Moo.

283
00:11:44,270 --> 00:11:47,373
Even I understand
about loneliness, Pixie.

284
00:11:47,373 --> 00:11:50,376
So why don't we all
just be friends?

285
00:11:50,376 --> 00:11:51,377
Chi?

286
00:11:51,377 --> 00:11:52,545
Foolishness!

287
00:11:52,545 --> 00:11:54,981
Pixie, we don't
have to be enemies.

288
00:11:54,981 --> 00:11:56,382
Do it!

289
00:11:56,382 --> 00:11:57,951
(shouting)

290
00:11:57,951 --> 00:12:02,555
♪

291
00:12:02,555 --> 00:12:04,557
Wonderful gesture,
Genki my boy,

292
00:12:04,557 --> 00:12:08,228
but I get the sense that
you didn't quite convince her.

293
00:12:08,228 --> 00:12:09,529
(shouting)

294
00:12:09,529 --> 00:12:11,764
Torpedo attack, Tiger!

295
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:15,301
Liberty!

296
00:12:15,301 --> 00:12:19,005
♪

297
00:12:19,005 --> 00:12:21,574
Whoa!

298
00:12:21,574 --> 00:12:23,543
(screaming)

299
00:12:23,543 --> 00:12:27,146
♪

300
00:12:27,146 --> 00:12:29,882
Hm...Big Blue?

301
00:12:29,882 --> 00:12:32,118
Giddyup!

302
00:12:33,686 --> 00:12:36,155
Hey, Pixie,
where are you going?

303
00:12:36,155 --> 00:12:37,223
Follow me.

304
00:12:37,223 --> 00:12:39,192
We've got too much entourage.

305
00:12:39,192 --> 00:12:41,294
Come on, let's go.

306
00:12:41,294 --> 00:12:44,097
♪

307
00:12:44,097 --> 00:12:46,232
So here we are, Pixie.

308
00:12:46,232 --> 00:12:48,835
♪

309
00:12:48,835 --> 00:12:51,738
Just listen, think for a second.

310
00:12:51,738 --> 00:12:54,340
We don't have to fight
if we choose not to.

311
00:12:54,340 --> 00:12:55,808
No one's making us.

312
00:12:55,808 --> 00:12:57,644
‐Do you get it?
‐Forget it!

313
00:12:57,644 --> 00:13:00,079
This one is mine.

314
00:13:00,079 --> 00:13:01,414
Giddyup!

315
00:13:01,414 --> 00:13:08,588
♪

316
00:13:08,588 --> 00:13:10,356
All right.

317
00:13:10,356 --> 00:13:13,526
♪

318
00:13:13,526 --> 00:13:15,228
Watch out!

319
00:13:16,429 --> 00:13:18,398
Torpedo!

320
00:13:18,398 --> 00:13:22,835
♪

321
00:13:22,835 --> 00:13:25,338
Tiger, no!

322
00:13:25,338 --> 00:13:27,006
I'm not done.

323
00:13:27,006 --> 00:13:28,641
You fool!

324
00:13:28,641 --> 00:13:34,080
♪

325
00:13:34,080 --> 00:13:35,515
Take this!

326
00:13:35,515 --> 00:13:38,518
Torpedo!

327
00:13:38,518 --> 00:13:39,819
Oh no you don't!

328
00:13:39,819 --> 00:13:44,457
You...got a... heart,
I know...you do!

329
00:13:44,457 --> 00:13:46,292
♪

330
00:13:46,292 --> 00:13:47,393
Fun?

331
00:13:47,393 --> 00:13:56,035
♪

332
00:13:56,035 --> 00:13:58,504
Just one more word...

333
00:13:58,504 --> 00:14:00,440
(shouting)

334
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:02,275
Chi!

335
00:14:02,275 --> 00:14:05,411
♪

336
00:14:05,411 --> 00:14:07,113
Lightning!

337
00:14:07,113 --> 00:14:09,449
(shouting)

338
00:14:09,449 --> 00:14:13,219
♪

339
00:14:13,219 --> 00:14:15,755
Air attack!

340
00:14:15,755 --> 00:14:18,458
They don't seem to know
when to quit, do they?

341
00:14:18,458 --> 00:14:21,027
♪

342
00:14:21,027 --> 00:14:22,495
Suezo!

343
00:14:22,495 --> 00:14:25,531
Pixie, please make
peace with the humans.

344
00:14:25,531 --> 00:14:28,067
Rocko and the other slaves
aren't like the humans

345
00:14:28,067 --> 00:14:29,936
that did you harm.

346
00:14:29,936 --> 00:14:32,505
Grudges are never good.

347
00:14:32,505 --> 00:14:35,541
They only give birth
to other grudges.

348
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:37,143
He's right.

349
00:14:37,143 --> 00:14:39,345
‐Be quiet.
‐Huh?

350
00:14:39,345 --> 00:14:42,014
‐Big Blue?
‐Giddyup!

351
00:14:42,014 --> 00:14:44,584
♪

352
00:14:44,584 --> 00:14:45,718
No, don't!

353
00:14:45,718 --> 00:14:47,987
Holly, this one is mine.

354
00:14:47,987 --> 00:14:49,422
You don't fight.

355
00:14:49,422 --> 00:14:50,590
Hurry!

356
00:14:50,590 --> 00:14:55,795
♪

357
00:15:00,733 --> 00:15:04,837
Golem, tornado!

358
00:15:04,837 --> 00:15:06,773
Should we be worried?

359
00:15:06,773 --> 00:15:08,107
Nah.

360
00:15:08,107 --> 00:15:24,457
♪

361
00:15:24,457 --> 00:15:26,426
I do not like fighting.

362
00:15:26,426 --> 00:15:28,394
It tears me apart.

363
00:15:28,394 --> 00:15:31,130
Big Blue, why don't
we discuss this

364
00:15:31,130 --> 00:15:33,866
like civilized Golems?

365
00:15:33,866 --> 00:15:35,101
(growls)

366
00:15:35,101 --> 00:15:36,536
Because!

367
00:15:36,536 --> 00:15:41,808
♪

368
00:15:41,808 --> 00:15:43,443
You okay?

369
00:15:43,443 --> 00:15:45,645
Fighting hurts.

370
00:15:45,645 --> 00:15:47,580
But... wait!

371
00:15:47,580 --> 00:15:49,715
Hand‐to‐hand, Big Blue.

372
00:15:49,715 --> 00:15:59,625
♪

373
00:15:59,625 --> 00:16:02,829
A group effort, how moving.

374
00:16:02,829 --> 00:16:07,500
♪

375
00:16:07,500 --> 00:16:09,368
All‐attack formation!

376
00:16:09,368 --> 00:16:27,286
♪

377
00:16:27,286 --> 00:16:29,255
How do you like this?

378
00:16:29,255 --> 00:16:30,790
What?

379
00:16:30,790 --> 00:16:33,926
♪

380
00:16:33,926 --> 00:16:35,728
Mocchi, blizzard!

381
00:16:35,728 --> 00:16:37,597
Chi!

382
00:16:37,597 --> 00:16:51,210
♪

383
00:16:51,210 --> 00:16:52,912
Nice try.

384
00:16:52,912 --> 00:16:55,815
Let's quit while
we're all ahead, Pixie.

385
00:16:55,815 --> 00:16:58,885
I'm not finished yet.

386
00:16:58,885 --> 00:17:02,021
You can't defeat us
because we're a team, Pixie.

387
00:17:02,021 --> 00:17:05,157
If one of us is down,
the others will step in.

388
00:17:05,157 --> 00:17:07,727
You've gotta see that.

389
00:17:07,727 --> 00:17:09,562
Ugh.

390
00:17:09,562 --> 00:17:11,364
Team this!

391
00:17:11,364 --> 00:17:13,332
(shouting)

392
00:17:13,332 --> 00:17:17,203
♪

393
00:17:17,203 --> 00:17:19,372
(rumbling)

394
00:17:19,372 --> 00:17:22,775
♪

395
00:17:22,775 --> 00:17:24,544
Oh no!

396
00:17:24,544 --> 00:17:26,178
The ruins!

397
00:17:26,178 --> 00:17:28,614
♪

398
00:17:28,614 --> 00:17:30,383
Run!

399
00:17:30,383 --> 00:17:33,185
♪

400
00:17:33,185 --> 00:17:35,321
Hey, Pixie, it's collapsing!

401
00:17:35,321 --> 00:17:37,056
Hurry up and escape!

402
00:17:37,056 --> 00:17:38,157
What's the point?

403
00:17:38,157 --> 00:17:40,059
Moo'll never
forgive me for this.

404
00:17:40,059 --> 00:17:43,095
Who really cares about Moo?

405
00:17:43,095 --> 00:17:44,931
(shouting)

406
00:17:44,931 --> 00:17:47,333
Master Pixie, no!

407
00:17:47,333 --> 00:17:50,403
♪

408
00:17:50,403 --> 00:17:52,705
(rumbling)

409
00:17:52,705 --> 00:17:54,674
Genki!

410
00:17:54,674 --> 00:18:13,025
♪

411
00:18:13,025 --> 00:18:14,560
(ax plinking into rock)

412
00:18:14,560 --> 00:18:15,695
Genki!

413
00:18:15,695 --> 00:18:19,165
Can you hear me?

414
00:18:19,165 --> 00:18:22,234
(all grunting)

415
00:18:22,234 --> 00:18:24,670
‐Mocchi, Mocchi!
‐Genki!

416
00:18:24,670 --> 00:18:28,274
♪

417
00:18:28,274 --> 00:18:31,477
I found them‐‐
here, come!

418
00:18:31,477 --> 00:18:33,346
(exclaiming)

419
00:18:33,346 --> 00:18:47,526
♪

420
00:18:47,526 --> 00:18:49,595
Hey!

421
00:18:50,396 --> 00:18:52,431
Well... did you win?

422
00:18:52,431 --> 00:18:53,332
Sort of.

423
00:18:53,332 --> 00:18:56,569
Actually, it was a tie, Pixie.

424
00:18:56,569 --> 00:18:58,037
Huh?

425
00:18:58,037 --> 00:19:04,777
♪

426
00:19:04,777 --> 00:19:07,380
Hey, Big Blue, thanks a lot.

427
00:19:07,380 --> 00:19:10,616
I was only
protecting Master Pixie.

428
00:19:10,616 --> 00:19:13,686
I was not trying
to save you, Genki.

429
00:19:13,686 --> 00:19:14,820
(Genki chuckles)

430
00:19:14,820 --> 00:19:16,922
Well, too bad,
you did anyway.

431
00:19:16,922 --> 00:19:24,730
♪

432
00:19:24,730 --> 00:19:27,133
What are you gonna
do now, Pixie?

433
00:19:27,133 --> 00:19:28,267
I don't know.

434
00:19:28,267 --> 00:19:30,269
Not much call for
defeated baddies,

435
00:19:30,269 --> 00:19:34,440
and Master Moo will
be after us soon.

436
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:36,776
If Moo's after you,
you must be a goody

437
00:19:36,776 --> 00:19:38,310
and not a baddie anymore,

438
00:19:38,310 --> 00:19:40,179
so why not come with us?

439
00:19:40,179 --> 00:19:45,017
♪

440
00:19:45,017 --> 00:19:47,853
Genki, I thank you
for risking your life

441
00:19:47,853 --> 00:19:50,056
to save mine, but...

442
00:19:50,056 --> 00:19:51,691
Don't get any ideas.

443
00:19:51,691 --> 00:19:54,460
The next time, we'll
beat you for sure.

444
00:19:54,460 --> 00:19:56,896
The both of you can always
join up with us later,

445
00:19:56,896 --> 00:19:58,097
if you want.

446
00:19:58,097 --> 00:20:00,866
Take care of yourselves,
good luck against Moo!

447
00:20:00,866 --> 00:20:02,101
Chi!

448
00:20:02,101 --> 00:20:04,203
They have to be silent.

449
00:20:04,203 --> 00:20:07,840
They only know how to wave
goodbye in their hearts.

450
00:20:07,840 --> 00:20:09,775
Nice.

451
00:20:09,775 --> 00:20:10,843
Hm.

452
00:20:10,843 --> 00:20:12,745
Adios, amigos.

453
00:20:12,745 --> 00:20:14,313
‐Rocko.
‐Huh?

454
00:20:14,313 --> 00:20:16,315
Shouldn't we go after them?

455
00:20:16,315 --> 00:20:18,951
Listen, if we take
revenge on Pixie,

456
00:20:18,951 --> 00:20:20,753
we'll be repeating
the same mistake

457
00:20:20,753 --> 00:20:24,957
that's gone on for
generation after generation.

458
00:20:24,957 --> 00:20:27,426
Maybe we can break the cycle.

459
00:20:27,426 --> 00:20:29,895
You're right.

460
00:20:29,895 --> 00:20:31,731
Goodbye!

461
00:20:31,731 --> 00:20:35,801
I sure hope you find whatever
it is you're looking for.

462
00:20:35,801 --> 00:20:37,970
Goodbye, chi!

463
00:20:37,970 --> 00:20:46,746
♪

464
00:20:46,746 --> 00:20:48,214
♪ Monsters ♪

465
00:20:48,214 --> 00:20:49,815
♪ Monsters rule ♪

466
00:20:49,815 --> 00:21:14,273
♪

467
00:21:14,273 --> 00:21:15,975
♪ Monsters rule ♪

